05/11/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- A parcel bomb addressed to the French Embassy in Athens was destroyed by police Thursday (November 4th) in a controlled explosion.
More than a dozen parcel bombs addressed to international organisations and embassies have been destroyed since Monday.
Authorities decided to resume international airmail as of Friday, following a 48-hour suspension.
Two Greeks in their 20s who allegedly handled some of the parcels are charged with committing acts of terrorism.
(AFP, BBC, Reuters - 04/11/10)
